description:
&lt;p&gt;There is an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated and enthusiastic RMN/OT to work in the Older Adult Home Treatment Service. Working as part of the Community Mental Health Team you will offer intensive support and treatment to patients in the community in the acute phase of a mental health crisis as an alternative to inpatient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will act as gate keepers to all admissions, attending Mental Health Act assessments and working closely with Psychiatric Liaison and other referrers. To reduce hospital stay you will also support early discharge from hospital. Staff will offer a service from 9.00am - 5.00pm - 7 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a range of post registration experience in Mental Health Nursing/OT. Experience of working with older people in a community setting would be desirable. You will have excellent communication and interpersonal skills, able to work as part of a MDT and provide high quality assessment and care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer regular clinical supervision and excellent professional developmental opportunities within a supportive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car owner &amp; driver essential&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 1 December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jennifer Grogan - CMHT HTS &amp; Memory Service Manager 01895 488998&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matt Jones – HTS Team Leader HTS 01895 488998&lt;/p&gt;
